rawContent:
So I have taken notice that the time frame for their current cycle of weekly and daily challenges keeps resetting itself in Rayman Legends.

I checked the trophy board and yes it is the truth (There should be Ubisoft symbol to separate the trophies of each cycle).

Loads of people are still doing the challenges because the same is happening to them, we all should be on Level 12 of Awesomeness and therefore, the only Trophy I need to get to get Platinum is to play a fried in the Kung foot football.. easily done just enable a second Playstation 4 controller and let myself win...

But all the same It's not everyday I stick to a game to platinum unless I really get lost in it.  And platinum Rayman Legends even without the cyber harassment is no easy feat.

It requires alot o patience especially the unlock the final character by collecting 1 Million Lums and reaching the Level 12 of Awesomeness.   Ubisoft pulled a cracker with Rayman Legends. 

I got for free Via PS Plus Subscription back in 2019.   

Another reason why I am not a trophy completion collector is because

Sony did not bring in the trophy collection system until I completed Uncharted Drakes Fortune 1.  Immediately after I completed Uncharted Drakes fortune like more less straight after.

When the trophies system came out I restarted Uncharted up and released that I had to play the game again to achieve the trophies as you cannot use your save data to backdate it all you have to earn the trophies when actually playing the game.

 I had just finished Uncharted and I was not in the mood to go through it again.  I was really annoyed at Sony in that moment and I even took it personally as it did feel personally.  No one knew abut the trophy system until the day Sony introduce it as a surprise.

That really put me off earning platinum trophies (You get by earning all the other trophies) games and that is the main reason, Sony did set a bad tone for it to be fair.. It was a surprise but they should have given people a head up, I'm sure I was not the only one who Sony PlayStation Annoyed at that time!

Plus I was wanting to get back to Fifa and Call of Duty Multiplayer gaming, on top of that you have to go in and out of the games to check the trophy list to see what you needed to do to get them.

You can print or buy trophy lists for individual games aswell, but being able to afford to buy new games and my own broadband and fiber broadband connection Multiplayer gaming in Cod Fifa and sometimes other games took hold of my interest.

Before the trophy system was introduced games like Marvel Ultimate Alliance and Heavenly Sword were games that I introduced which also played a major a factor in me just being deflated around the trophy system.  I'm on a backlog at the moment.

Some people do the trophy Platinum completion  to add interest to gaming and to be honest I getting to that point aswell.   Some do it because they have families and well you can't exactly pause an online gaming session without everyone else stopping and in Fifa you get 3 pauses which are 30 seconds.  These people have their priorities straight.  Good to see aswell I am giving them an honest good witness.

Then there is the people like GS (At least one point in the past) who do it because they can never afford the appropriate internet connection (Unlimited Data) or money to buy new games when they want to.  They have to stick to one game for a long period of time before the get a new one.

For a while I would pay for the broadband out of my Bank Account via Direct Debit in which the broadband would be under my Mums name ( I do not know if you can still do that.  Of course eventually as I built up credit I was able to get Sky TV and Sky broadband under my name in which I would also pat for both and of course allow my Mum to use both aswell (Broadband was unlimited Data)

Now people seek to destroy my credit altogether in the name of petty Jealousy and of Course a Means to help Gary Shaw.  It's fucking pathetic...

Paying my Mum ¬£130 House keep money + Paying for the Sky TV and Sky Broadband Subscription is exactly how I paid my house keep.

It got to the point at the end of 2019 I started to get suspicious of the ¬£130 cash payment with the new knowledge I had obtained that year (As it was at that point) I started paying for the Gas and Electric each week.

Each week I would pay ¬£15 Gas and ¬£15 electric into the house 

30x4 = ¬£120, some months have that extra week, so some months have 5 weeks so it all would get back dated anyway then on top of that the then Virgin TV Subscription and Virgin Broadband Subscription for both me and my Mum to use.  It was under my name.
